Knights of Columbus

From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia
  (Redirected from Knight of Columbus)

					Jump to:					navigation, 					search

Not to be confused with Knights of St Columba.

Knights of Columbus


Emblem of the Knights of Columbus



Abbreviation
K of C


Motto
In service to One,
In service to all.


Formation
March 29, 1882; 135 years ago (1882-03-29)


Type
Catholic fraternal service organization


Headquarters
1 Columbus Plaza,
New Haven, Connecticut, USA



